Bug 1675937 - Keep a calendar in its place in the calendar list when it is re-created or re-registered, instead of dropping it to the bottom. r=aleca

Toggling a calendar's offline support re-creates it under a new id, and enabling or disabling a calendar provider re-registers its calendars. Either way the calendar is unregistered and registered again, and `addCalendarItem` appended the new row at the end while `saveSortOrder` persisted that order, so the calendar dropped to the bottom of the list.

The manager already records the previous position in the `initialSortOrderPos` property, but nothing read it. On re-registration, read it and insert the row at that position; a freshly built list still appends in `calendar.list.sortOrder` order, so a leftover value cannot misplace a row in a newly opened window.

When a provider owns several calendars, re-register them in list order so they keep their relative order instead of being reinserted in cache order.

Mark `initialSortOrderPos` transient so this position hint is not written to prefs.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310646


